java.util.zip

Class InflaterInputStream

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.io.InputStream
      • java.io.FilterInputStream
        • java.util.zip.InflaterInputStream
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    GZIPInputStream, ZipInputStream

    public class InflaterInputStream
extends FilterInputStream
    This class implements a stream filter for uncompressing data in the "deflate" compression format. It is also used as the basis for other decompression filters, such as GZIPInputStream. NOTE: java.util.zip.GZIPInputStream is found in J2ME CDC profiles such as J2ME Foundation Profile.
    Version:
    1.28, 02/02/00
    Author:
    David Connelly
    See Also:
    Inflater

      • available

        public int available()
              throws IOException
        Returns 0 after EOF has reached, otherwise always return 1.

        Programs should not count on this method to return the actual number of bytes that could be read without blocking.

        Overrides:
